this extracts the low-risk, self-contained, ready-to-go stuff from https://github.com/grafana/grafana/pull/118825.

this PR can be reviewed one commit at a time, or one file at a time. (each commit optimizes a single file)

the last commit (https://github.com/grafana/grafana/commit/f6bb1644741e258b0db0dfddc41a505cadbed6b4) needs a bit more explanation:

because of this dependency: https://github.com/grafana/grafana/blob/5b3df36b4a1d782c609100e5cd956633888e2714/public/app/plugins/panel/timeseries/plugins/AnnotationsPlugin2.tsx#L246

we cannot do `data.annotations ?? []` since in the absence of `data.annotations` this creates a new array and forces an additional redraw on every panel rerender.

https://github.com/grafana/grafana/blob/5b3df36b4a1d782c609100e5cd956633888e2714/public/app/plugins/panel/timeseries/TimeSeriesPanel.tsx#L222

the dashboard datasource seems to have the same pattern of always re-creating the annos array, too:

https://github.com/search?q=repo%3Agrafana%2Fgrafana+%22data.annotations+%3F%3F+%5B%5D%22&type=code

---

for a 2,000 series x 1,440pt dataset...

- **cpu drops by 55%**
- **memory drops by 170MB**.

