* `HasChildPathFailedUpdate` is used as a safety gate before deleting old folders, but `failedUpdates` is only populated when `result.Error() != nil`. If an update failure is classified as a warning (e.g., validation/ownership/quota warning via `WithError`), it won’t be tracked and `deleteFolders` may still delete the old folder even though a child re-parent/update didn’t actually succeed. Consider also tracking update *warnings* (at least for `FileActionUpdated`) in `failedUpdates`, or adjust `deleteFolders` to treat update warnings under the folder as a blocking condition.
```
		// Track failed updates so we can block folder cleanup when child re-parenting fails
		if result.Action() == repository.FileActionUpdated {
			r.failedUpdates = append(r.failedUpdates, result.Path())
		}
	} else if result.Warning() != nil {
		// Still track failed deletions in case we get a warning
